---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Cyber" description="Cyber and technical projects — Spencerprod portfolio.">
	<p class="section-eyebrow">Cyber projects</p>
	<h1>Security, code, and systems</h1>
	<p class="section-lede">
		A home for labs, tooling, and writeups. Below is sample layout—drop in repos, demos, and case studies when you are ready.
	</p>

	<p class="ph-callout">
		<strong>Placeholder content.</strong> Replace these cards with real project titles, screenshots, and links to GitHub or live demos.
	</p>

	<h2 class="ph-block-title">Featured work</h2>
	<div class="ph-grid">
		<article class="ph-card">
			<div class="ph-pills">
				<span class="ph-pill">Lab</span>
				<span class="ph-pill">Network</span>
			</div>
			<h3>Home network segmentation</h3>
			<p>
				Example blurb: VLAN layout, firewall rules, and how you document changes. Swap this for your own project summary.
			</p>
		</article>
		<article class="ph-card">
			<div class="ph-pills">
				<span class="ph-pill">Write-up</span>
				<span class="ph-pill">CTF</span>
			</div>
			<h3>Challenge: “Locker” walkthrough</h3>
			<p>
				Placeholder for a CTF or bug-bounty style post—tools used, key insight, and what you learned.
			</p>
		</article>
		<article class="ph-card">
			<div class="ph-pills">
				<span class="ph-pill">Tooling</span>
				<span class="ph-pill">WIP</span>
			</div>
			<h3>CLI helper: log tail + filter</h3>
			<p>
				Short pitch for a script or app you built. Link to <code>README</code> or a demo recording when you publish it.
			</p>
		</article>
	</div>

	<h2 class="ph-block-title">Stack & focus (sample)</h2>
	<ul class="ph-list">
		<li>Linux, scripting, and automation</li>
		<li>Defensive tooling and logging</li>
		<li>Secure defaults for personal infrastructure</li>
	</ul>
</Layout>
